1
00:00:19,220 --> 00:00:22,040
Why do you think
I let you go in the first place?

2
00:00:22,390 --> 00:00:23,440
Please.

3
00:00:25,310 --> 00:00:26,900
You have to be happy.

4
00:00:32,690 --> 00:00:38,020
My happiness
is fulfilling your wishes.

5
00:00:40,420 --> 00:00:41,620
If that's what you want...

6
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:45,440
I can arrange for you
to return to the company.

7
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:49,039
Whether it's destroying the people
who kicked you out or anything else...

8
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:50,730
Just give me the order.

9
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:56,820
Takaaki said something so terrifying
with a completely straight face.

10
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:01,030
So, what is your order?

11
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:02,640
Forever...

12
00:01:04,340 --> 00:01:05,540
Stay by my side forever.

13
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,330
He listened to my answer.

14
00:01:10,603 --> 00:01:13,610
And started coming to
my place three days a week.

15
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:23,760
Since then, I haven't
given Takaaki a single order.

16
00:01:37,980 --> 00:01:43,260
Even so, Takaaki still takes care of me
just like before.

17
00:01:47,020 --> 00:01:50,610
The only difference is...

18
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,280
We haven't slept together.

19
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:56,700
"The Servant Prince"
(Episode 2)

20
00:02:58,340 --> 00:03:00,200
Are you still working on that?

21
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:09,140
Do you really need to dry
that plate so thoroughly?

22
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,190
I'm almost done.

23
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:14,980
Damn it.

24
00:03:16,060 --> 00:03:17,230
What should I do?

25
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:20,210
Before, whenever I wanted to do it,
I'd just get ready...

26
00:03:20,570 --> 00:03:22,820
And then I'd just order him.

27
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,640
Come here.

28
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,040
Let's do it.

29
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,500
Understood.

30
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:38,420
Other than that,
I have no idea how to initiate it.

31
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,860
Is something wrong?

32
00:03:48,450 --> 00:03:49,450
It's nothing.

33
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,520
Um...

34
00:03:57,980 --> 00:03:59,030
Naoya?

35
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:03,610
Beer.

36
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:16,726
Once I finish cleaning up here,
I'll dry your hair for you.

37
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:17,750
No, thanks.

38
00:04:19,210 --> 00:04:20,590
I can do it myself.

39
00:04:24,820 --> 00:04:25,820
Oh, man.

40
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,070
This is bad.

41
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:31,890
He was cute enough before, but...

42
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,379
Hey, what are you doing?

43
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:36,380
Hurry up and do it.

44
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:38,840
Understood.

45
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:44,170
This is way cuter
than I ever imagined.

46
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:48,940
Honestly...

47
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:51,220
I want to pin him down right now.

48
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:59,280
If he'd just give me one order...

49
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,459
You haven't dried your hair yet, have you?

50
00:05:08,460 --> 00:05:09,460
It's fine.

51
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,619
You'll catch a cold if you leave it wet.

52
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:13,340
I said I've got it.

53
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,540
Hey, Takaaki.

54
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:25,230
When do you usually feel like doing it?

55
00:06:30,150 --> 00:06:34,240
Whenever you order me to.
Anytime is fine.

56
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:46,730
If you don't want to, then never mind.

57
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:01,020
Naoya, you've got it wrong.

58
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,650
I've always been
in a state of "waiting."

59
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:08,940
What?

60
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:13,700
I'm always waiting for you
to give me the green light.

61
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,450
You ask when I feel like doing it?

62
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:21,260
As long as it's you, Naoya,
I want to all the time.

63
00:07:23,810 --> 00:07:26,330
If you let me touch you
without waiting for an order...

64
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,880
You'll definitely regret it.

65
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,300
You...

66
00:07:38,210 --> 00:07:39,510
Back in high school...

67
00:07:41,370 --> 00:07:42,370
Here.

68
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:46,150
Lick it clean.

69
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:52,500
Naoya's orders were always the best reward for
someone constantly suppressing his desires.

70
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:55,350
Understood.

71
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:13,520
You really do
whatever I say, don't you?

72
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:19,700
If I ordered you to kiss me,
would you do that too?

73
00:09:00,090 --> 00:09:01,120
What is your order?

74
00:09:08,380 --> 00:09:09,380
Today...

75
00:09:11,210 --> 00:09:13,440
Do it until you're satisfied.

76
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:17,860
So cute.

77
00:09:21,830 --> 00:09:22,930
Understood.

78
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,830
Even when I was tormented
by near-fatal despair...

79
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,790
He would hold me
until I drifted off to sleep.

80
00:09:55,310 --> 00:09:56,550
And when I woke up...

81
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:04,140
I'd feel like I could keep going.

82
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:41,500
(Goto Construction)

83
00:10:41,890 --> 00:10:43,240
That company name...

84
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,060
Isn't that my parents' company?

85
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,020
Good morning.

86
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:49,520
Don't "good morning" me.

87
00:10:50,210 --> 00:10:51,439
Are you doing business with them?

88
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:54,189
I told you, whether you want to go back
or crush them, I'll do whatever you order.

89
00:10:54,190 --> 00:10:55,670
I've already laid the groundwork.

90
00:10:56,930 --> 00:11:00,510
What you said back then...
you actually had a concrete plan?

91
00:11:18,286 --> 00:11:19,426
You're burning up.

92
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:28,030
You have a slight fever.

93
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,240
You should rest today.

94
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:33,900
It doesn't matter what day it is.

95
00:11:34,270 --> 00:11:36,220
Every day is a day off for the unemployed.

96
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:37,780
Get some proper rest.

97
00:11:38,650 --> 00:11:40,150
Stop treating me like a child.

98
00:11:42,190 --> 00:11:43,240
Be good.

99
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,550
Unemployed...

100
00:12:04,370 --> 00:12:06,260
Living in a studio
apartment provided for me.

101
00:12:09,490 --> 00:12:13,370
With this body that can only survive
by relying on someone else...

102
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:27,100
Can I ever pull myself
out of this rock bottom...

103
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:33,040
And return to normal society?

104
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:43,010
I want to...

105
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,010
become strong too.

106
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:56,270
Yes.

107
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,570
Just like Takaaki.

108
00:13:00,530 --> 00:13:03,210
Just like my father,
whom I could never resist.

109
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:08,300
Even though I know
I'm not cut out for it...

110
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:14,140
I just can't bring myself to give up.

111
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:25,860
Understood.

112
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:24,690
Damn it...

113
00:14:27,420 --> 00:14:28,420
It's delicious.

114
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:45,320
Understood.

115
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:52,240
He said "Understood" at the end...

116
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:57,240
But even so, there's probably
nothing I can do.

117
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:13,620
Well, that concludes our regular meeting.

118
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:15,800
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

119
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:33,680
Hey.

120
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,390
Is this a good time to talk?

121
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:38,230
Oh, what a surprise.

122
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,020
I didn't expect you to call me.

123
00:15:41,850 --> 00:15:43,890
I thought I'd better make things clear.

124
00:15:45,540 --> 00:15:46,540
About last night...

125
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:50,100
Actually, this morning too.
Forget all of it.

126
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,600
Wipe it completely from your memory.

127
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:54,560
Forget what?

128
00:15:56,540 --> 00:15:57,840
Everything, you idiot!

129
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,560
Understood.

130
00:16:09,090 --> 00:16:10,130
Damn it...

131
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:14,050
I'm not letting him
have his way with me anymore.

132
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:23,520
*Sigh*

133
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:28,480
"I want to become strong," my foot.

134
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:36,120
No matter how you look at it, I should
start by learning to support myself.

135
00:16:45,940 --> 00:16:46,940
All right.

136
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:05,400
(President Goto Taketoshi)

137
00:17:10,073 --> 00:17:15,603
Two years ago, on the day Naoya called me
to say he had lost everything...

138
00:17:21,310 --> 00:17:22,350
Naoya.

139
00:17:24,370 --> 00:17:25,560
Takaaki.

140
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:31,060
Sell this apartment as soon as possible
and find me a cheap studio.

141
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:36,400
Anywhere is fine,
as long as it's out of the way.

142
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:41,140
If there's nothing left after paying off
the mortgage, I need you to cover the rest.

143
00:17:43,940 --> 00:17:47,960
Once the bankruptcy is finalized,
I'll move in immediately.

144
00:17:53,780 --> 00:17:54,780
Understood.

145
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:16,800
Everything here is exactly the same
as it was when I came by two days ago.

146
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:26,120
Takaaki, you're here.

147
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,870
You should eat something.

148
00:18:30,020 --> 00:18:31,020
No.

149
00:18:34,050 --> 00:18:35,540
I called you here to sleep with me.

150
00:18:38,370 --> 00:18:39,370
Now...

151
00:18:40,130 --> 00:18:41,470
Go take a shower.

152
00:18:45,410 --> 00:18:46,460
Understood.

153
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:24,340
While I held him...

154
00:19:25,570 --> 00:19:29,560
He cried himself to sleep.

155
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:38,260
It was a cycle that kept repeating.

156
00:19:41,970 --> 00:19:43,150
Excuse me.

157
00:19:43,610 --> 00:19:45,669
President, the car is ready.

158
00:19:45,670 --> 00:19:46,990
Good. Thank you.

159
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:15,810
Regarding the matter we
discussed the other day...

160
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:19,020
Here are the compiled details.

161
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:34,660
I see.

162
00:20:35,090 --> 00:20:38,110
From our standpoint,
we cannot make any further concessions.

163
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:41,380
You're talking pretty big.

164
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:45,470
I hear you're also considering
partnering with other companies.

165
00:20:48,490 --> 00:20:50,160
You're well-informed.

166
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:52,289
It would be a shame, but...

167
00:20:52,290 --> 00:20:54,369
If you insist on forcing through
your original budget...

168
00:20:54,370 --> 00:20:56,530
We'll have no choice but
to terminate our partnership.

169
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,770
Are you sure you want to say that?

170
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:02,520
You're just a newly established startup.

171
00:21:03,930 --> 00:21:05,860
If you lose your contract with our group...

172
00:21:06,690 --> 00:21:10,560
Your cash flow will dry up,
and you'll be ruined in no time.

173
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:12,530
You don't need to worry about that.

174
00:21:15,430 --> 00:21:17,330
Please give it some thought.

175
00:21:33,870 --> 00:21:35,040
Over the past two years...

176
00:21:35,490 --> 00:21:37,270
as Naoya's hair grew longer...

177
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,350
his mind and body slowly began to heal.

178
00:21:42,130 --> 00:21:43,130
But...

179
00:21:44,910 --> 00:21:48,510
Sell this apartment as soon as possible
and find me a cheap studio.

180
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:49,760
Takaaki, you're here.

181
00:21:49,810 --> 00:21:51,229
You should eat something.

182
00:21:51,230 --> 00:21:52,230
No.

183
00:21:53,690 --> 00:21:55,120
I called you here to sleep with me.

184
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:58,350
Please.

185
00:21:59,163 --> 00:22:00,863
You have to be happy.

186
00:22:02,070 --> 00:22:03,070
I want to...

187
00:22:04,710 --> 00:22:06,920
Become strong too.

188
00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:21,650
The people who pushed Naoya to the edge...

189
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,270
I will never forgive them.

190
00:22:45,602 --> 00:22:51,342
[He's scrolling through
part-time job applications]

191
00:22:56,229 --> 00:23:03,902
[A listing for a wait-staff position
at a Western style restaurant]

192
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:15,900
(Preview)

193
00:24:15,910 --> 00:24:18,556
My name is Goto Naoya, and I start working
here today. It's a pleasure to meet you.

194
00:24:18,580 --> 00:24:21,579
Wow, Goto-kun
is a natural at this.

195
00:24:21,580 --> 00:24:22,849
Well, if it isn't Naoya.

196
00:24:22,850 --> 00:24:24,959
I wondered where you'd been hiding.

197
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:29,060
I never expected to find you here, doing
grunt work that even a monkey could do.

198
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:30,270
Goto-kun.

199
00:24:31,010 --> 00:24:32,579
Will I see you tomorrow too?

200
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:34,140
Yes, I'm on the schedule.

201
00:24:34,220 --> 00:24:36,129
Did something happen?

202
00:24:36,130 --> 00:24:38,390
Hey, hold me.

203
00:24:39,210 --> 00:24:40,830
You can do whatever you want with me.

204
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:44,100
I'm the only one he has left.

